# Tech Stack Conventions

## Core Stack

### NestJS (^10.x ŌĆö Ghostfolio's version)
- Use decorators: `@Module`, `@Controller`, `@Injectable`, `@Get`, `@Post`, `@UseGuards`
- All services must be `@Injectable()` and registered as providers in their module
- Use constructor injection for all dependencies ŌĆö never instantiate services directly
- Mirror existing patterns in `apps/api/src/app/endpoints/` for new endpoints
- Reference: https://docs.nestjs.com

### TypeScript (^5.x)
- Strict mode: no `any` types ŌĆö use `unknown` with type guards when the type is truly unknown
- Use interfaces for contracts, types for unions/intersections
- Prefer `readonly` for properties that should not be reassigned
- All function parameters and return types must be explicitly typed
- Use barrel exports (`index.ts`) for public module APIs

### Nx (Ghostfolio's version)
- Respect project boundaries: `apps/api` imports from `libs/common`, not from `apps/client`
- Use `libs/common` for shared interfaces and types
- Run tasks via Nx: `npx nx test api`, `npx nx lint api`
- Reference: https://nx.dev/getting-started/intro

### Prisma (Ghostfolio's version)
- Use the existing `PrismaService` ŌĆö never create raw SQL queries
- All database access goes through Ghostfolio's existing service layer (PortfolioService, OrderService, etc.)
- The agent does NOT modify data ŌĆö all access is read-only
- Reference: https://www.prisma.io/docs

## AI / Agent Stack

### Vercel AI SDK (`ai` v4.3.16 ŌĆö already installed)
- Use `generateText()` with `maxSteps` for agentic tool-calling loops
- Use `tool()` helper to define tools with Zod schemas
- Use `generateObject()` only when structured output is required without tool-calling
- Access token usage from response: `result.usage.promptTokens`, `result.usage.completionTokens`
- Import from `ai`: `import { generateText, tool } from 'ai'`
- Reference: https://sdk.vercel.ai/docs

### OpenRouter Provider (`@openrouter/ai-sdk-provider` v0.7.2 ŌĆö already installed)
- Use `createOpenRouter()` to create the provider instance
- Pin model: `anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet` (or the model set in admin panel)
- API key is stored in Ghostfolio's PropertyService as `PROPERTY_API_KEY_OPENROUTER`
- Import: `import { createOpenRouter } from '@openrouter/ai-sdk-provider'`
- Reference: https://openrouter.ai/docs

### Zod (^3.x ŌĆö already installed)
- Define all tool input/output schemas with Zod
- Use `.describe()` on every schema field ŌĆö these descriptions are LLM prompts
- Export both the schema and the inferred TypeScript type: `z.infer<typeof MySchema>`
- Reference: https://zod.dev

### Langfuse (post-MVP ŌĆö Epic 11)
- Not used during MVP phase
- When integrated: use `@langfuse/vercel` for Vercel AI SDK trace wrapping
- Reference: https://langfuse.com/docs

## Testing

### Jest (Ghostfolio's version)
- Test files: `*.spec.ts` co-located with source files
- Use `describe` / `it` blocks with clear test names
- Mock external services with `jest.fn()` or NestJS `Test.createTestingModule`
- Follow TDD: write the failing test first, then implement
- Reference: https://jestjs.io/docs/getting-started

## MVP Observability (console-level)

Until Langfuse is wired (post-MVP), all agent-related services should log structured data to console using NestJS `Logger`:
- Tool calls: name, args summary, result success/fail, latency in ms
- LLM calls: model, input/output token counts, latency
- Verification: checker name, pass/fail, reason on failure
- Errors: error type, user-facing message, stack trace at debug level

```typescript
import { Logger } from '@nestjs/common';
const logger = new Logger('AgentService');
logger.log(`Tool call: ${toolName} completed in ${ms}ms (success: ${result.success})`);
```
